member.name: T:TestFramework.PluginTestCell.ITestCellInterface
member.summary: The implementation of this interface builds the TestFramework plugin interface of a test cell.
member.remarks: This interface needs to be implemented by a every plugin test cell as 'TestFrameworkPlugin.TestCell'. The name of the root namespace must be 'TestFrameworkPlugin' and the name of the class must be 'TestCell'. The implementation of method 'Configure' is optional all other methods must be implemented. To implement a subset of the methods a TestCell class without implementing ITestCellInterface could be defined. Loading the TestCell plugin the TestFramework will analyse the TestCell class. Only implemented methods will be used.

member.returns: Info text describing the test cell.

member.name: M:TestFramework.PluginTestCell.ITestCellInterface.Run(TestFramework.PluginTestCell.TestCellEnvironment,System.String,System.String)
member.summary: Runs the test cell.
member.param: An argument related to the command
member.remarks: This method will be called by the TestFramework to run the test cell. Commands and arguments can be used to control the test cell plugin. Syntax and functions can be freely defined by the implementation of the plugin. Merely the command prefix "TFW." is reserved for internal purposes and should not be used. If the Run method is called from the tester software user interface the command is "TFW.OpenProject" and the argument is the project name.

member.name: M:TestFramework.PluginTestCell.Project.GetItem(System.String)
member.summary: Gets a root level item.
member.remarks:
The data items are building a recursive data structure. Any item can contain sub-items itself. Method GetItem returns the requested sub-item. Item names can be concatenated with dots to a combined query.
item = args.Data.GetItem("ItemA").GetItem("ItemB") ' the same query combined: item = args.Data.GetItem("ItemA.ItemB")
If a requested item does not exist a special 'Null-Item' object will be returned. A Null-Item can be detected requesting the boolean property "#IsNull".
is_null = CType(args.Data.GetItem("ItemA").GetProperty("#IsNull"), Boolean)
Items can contain a list of sub-items which can be querried by it's index. The number of sub-items can be find out by requesting the integer property "#Count".
For i as Integer = 0 to CType(args.Data.GetItem("ItemC").GetProperty("#Count"), Integer) item = args.Data.GetItem("ItemC", i) Next
Any item can contain property values. Method GetProperty returns the requested property value.
value = args.Data.GetItem("ItemA").GetProperty("PropA")
If a requested property does not exist a special 'Null-Property' object will be returned. The ToString method of the Null-Property always returns the empyt string. To detect if a property exists request the property with the argument "#IsNull".
is_null = CType(args.Data.GetItem("ItemA").GetProperty("PropA", "#IsNull"), Boolean)
The provided data structure:
Item ProjectData
Sub-Item TestFramework - The frameworks's properties.
Sub-Item BoardData - The board's master data.
Sub-Item FixtureData - The fixture's master data.
Sub-Item TestData - The test program's master data.
Sub-Item TestResult - The results of the last test run.
Item TestFramework
Property AttachedProjects as string array - The names of the attached projects.
Item TestData - The test program's master data.
Sub-Item TestSection(TestSectionName as string) - The master data of a test section.
Sub-Item TestStep(TestStepRecordID as integer) - The master data of a test step.
Property ProjectName as string - The name of the test project.
Item TestSection - The master data of a test section.
Property BoardName as string - The name of board the test section is assigned to.
Item TestStep - The master data of a test step.
Sub-Item Properties - The properties (parameters) defined for the test step.
Sub-Item TestChannels - The test step's test channel data.
Property TestSectionName - The name of the test section containing the test step.
Property TemplateName - The name of the test step's test template.
Property PropertyNames as string array - The names of all test step properties (parameters).
Item Properties - The properties (parameters) defined for the test step.
Property {any property defined for the test step}(Selector as string)
Selector Type - GetProperty will return the type name of the parameter as one of the following strings: Boolean, Enumeration, Float, Integer, IntegerArray, Text, TestChannel, Tolerance, None.
Selector {empty} - GetProperty will return the property's value. A Boolean type will be returned as boolean, a Float type as double, an Integer type as integer, an IntegerArray type as integer array and all others as string.
Item TestChannels - The test channels of a a test step.
Property All as integer array - All nail numbers of all test channel parameters.
Property Stimulus as integer array - Nail numbers of all test channel parameters where the name contains the pattern "Force" or "Sense" but not "Guard".
Property Guard as integer array - Nail numbers of all test channel parameters where the name contains the pattern "Guard".
Item FixtureData - The fixture's master data.
Sub-Item Nail(NailNumber as integer) - A fixture nail's data. (Note: Nail is not a sub-item list and NailNumber is not and index.)
Item Nail - The fixture nail's master data.
Property Number as integer - The nail number.
Property NetName as string - The name of the contacted net.
Property TestPointName as string - The name of the contacted test point.
Item TestResult - The test result data.
Sub-Item RunResult - The result data of the last test run.
Item RunResult - The result data of a test run. Only the result data of the most recently executed project is available!
Sub-Item List Steps(Index as integer) - The test result data of a test step.
Property TotalResult as ResultState - The total test result of the test run.
Item Step - The test result data of a test step.
Sub-Item List Results(Index as integer) - The test results of the step.
Property ResultState as ResultState - The total result state of the step.
Item Result - The test result data of a test step.
Property ResultState as ResultState - The result state.
Property BoardName as string - The name of the tested board.
Property BoardTypeName as string - The name of the tested board type.
Property TestedPart as string - The name of the tested part.
Property TestedPin as string - The name of the tested pin.
Property Variant as string - The selected board variant.
Property TestStepName as string - The test step name.
Property TestStepRecordID as int - The record id of the test step (use as argument in TestData query).
Property TestStepLogInfo as string - The log info text of the test step.
Property NominalValue as double - The nominal value for the measurement.
Property ResultValue as double - The measurement value.
Property ResultValueText as string - The measurement value as formatted text.
Property ResultValueLowerLimit as double - The lower limit for a good measurement value.
Property ResultValueUpperLimit as double - The upper limit for a good measurement value.
Property ResultValueUnit as PhysicalUnit - The physical unit of the measurement value.
Property ResultValueState as ResultValueState - The state of the measurement.
Property ResultInfo as string - The remark text for the result.
Property NodeA as string - The first tested node (shorts test).
Property NodeB as string - The second tested node (shorts test).
Property FixtureNail as integer - The tested fixture nail (contact test).
ResultState, ResultValueState and PhysicalUnit are members of TestFramework.PluginTestCell.TestResults.
